pageContext.description: Dimensions: Width: m. 38.3mm; Wbl. 49.8; Wlp 10; B.m. 34; D.S. 66.5,Depression in m. - cg. flaw; v. thin s. end; 3 med. short ribs on either face - evenly spaced; rib-emph. body corners; spaced double m-m; tr. cg. fl. - little off centre on reverse side.
pageContext.patina: Fragments of dark brown patina; much flaked to rough paler brown sur.
pageContext.surface: Edge gold - cut sq. in recent times; parts of faces also rubbed to golden brown; traces fawn and orangey matrix adhering.
pageContext.collection: Stanier, Sir A. - Private (no. 4),The Manor, East Farndon, Market Harborough, Leics.
pageContext.site: Unprovenanced,possibly from the vicinity of the Red Castle, Weston-under-Redcastle, Salop.
